text-unit.text: In the quaint village of Greenwood, nestled at the edge of a whispering forest,a unique tradition hasbeen thriving for cen-turies. Every spring, thevillagers gather to cel-ebrate the Festival of Blooms,a vibrant event markedby an explosion of col-ors and scents. The fes-tival centers around thecompetition of floral ar-rangements, where par-ticipants from all age groupsdisplay their creativitywith flowers handpickedfrom the surrounding woods.The air is filled with thesweet fragrance of wild roses, lilacs, and jasmine, mingling with the sound oflaughter and folk music. Children dart between stalls, their faces painted withpetal motifs, while elders share stories of festivals past. The highlight of theevent is the crowning of the Bloom Queen, a title bestowed upon the creatorof the most breathtaking floral display.
